result.formatted_address: 30號 Sung Chi St, Hok Yuen, Hong Kong
result.name: Eight Station Cafe

reviews.text: Good food with reasonable price

Came here by coincidence, attracted by the menu and the boss of the restaurant, it just opened since 11days. The recommended menu are the Porks, from Spain. It’s best way to test the restaurant with the recommended dishes. 
Started with Garlic bread and soup, the garlic bread is hot, it’s very sincere cooking, most of the restaurants serve the crab breads, either hard like stone, or dry, cold. This one is just fine. The soup was made of carrots, surprised again. I couldn’t know what was it, but after the explained by the chef, then realised it’s carrot, frankly speaking, I don’t like carrots but like this soup.
The main course arrived with nice scents, the Pork chop is thick and firm, but it’s easily cut by knife, the taste is different to any normal Cha Tsan Ting. The aroma of the pork chop can be even better if try to cook one side with a bit burned. 
The set dinner also come with famous dessert “The heart is too soft”. Ha ha, this is really nice. I think the best way to find out is to try it. Set dinner only 128. Will come to try the beef next time. 
Hope the chef can keep it up. Good luck.
Good for rest and drinks
